{
  "texts": [
    "It transcends the traditional layered protocol model, thereby enhancing the flexibility of service composition.",
    "This flexibility manifests in the number of services that can be assembled as needed and in the invocation relationships between services.",
    "By executing multiple services in parallel, processing efficiency can be considerably enhanced (Fig. 15).",
    "For instance, the current PDCP layer performs integrity protection, followed by encryption and addition of PDCP headers.",
    "The encryption primarily targets Internet protocol (IP) and its upper-layer packet headers as well as data fields."
  ]
}